AGI -&nbsp; therefore I am. The beauty that shines in the Vatican seems to me: bring the pilgrim to “feel” and affirm his faith without suffocating it with the laces of reason. According to a conception of art, the beauty gives shape to the divine. And the parish church leaves the pilgrim really amazed >, beauty can be a fabulous flying carpet to carry the soul beyond. In the church, the Confession (and the tomb of Peter) is one of the destinations to reach.
Following the central nave, the work is located in the cavity under the Baldacchino, while at the top rises the michelangiolesca dome where the words of Jesus to the apostle are reported: “You are Peter and on this stone I will build my church, you are the keys to the Kingdom of Heaven.” >
Each element of the artistic picture is in its place, as in a constellation: at the bottom is the Confession, at the center the papal altar and above the declaration “celeste”. From Heaven to Earth. The deep sense of Confession comes from afar, from the Jewish tradition. Our “big brothers” > (as Pope Wojtyla called them) celebrate it with Yom Kippur (Festa dell'Espiazione). In the temple > the high priest pronounced the name of God symbolically pouring out the sins of the community on a goat (called atonement) sent to die in the desert. Another animal itself was instead swallowed and sacrificed to the Lord. As catechism explains, in Christianity the scapegoat is Christ embodied: He was crucified for the salvation of all. >
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Moreover, there is an element to which the Church recommends to pay particular attention. The biblical transgression that prompted the chase from the Eden of Adam and Eve left in the human soul an always open wound, the tendency to evil. It is almost a brand, a stigma, a sign of recognition that explains the vulnerability of each one to think and act in an inconvenience. Therefore religion warns: the continuous negative manifestation risks to vanify the sacrifice of Christ. It would be like a vaccine that would stop protecting from a virus because you don't do any more booster doses. So what's the remedy? It's a rite.
The Church repeats it every year precisely because the saving energies of Christ are not dispersed. It consists in (re)protecting one's faith on Easter night, at the Feast of Light. On that occasion the priest celebrates the Resurrection of Jesus, he baptizes new Christians and asks who is already to reiterate the commitment assumed (by his parents) with the first sacrament, Baptism. To reaffirm one's Creed is to keep alive the flame of faith. And it is not a case if ways and time established for the celebration are a wake at night. Another metaphor: without Christ on men it would be dark.
